[1
Date: Wed, 09 Sep 1998 13:44:38 -0500
Source: India Daily Internet Edition - 8 September
Via: Clyde Markon <docmarkon@worldnet.att.net>

Government claims dip in epidemic as two more die in the Capital
Even as the Delhi government claimed that there was a decrease in the new
patients of epidemic dropsy, two more persons died due to the disease. With
this, 52 people have died in the Capital due to dropsy, which has left over
2,200 people ill in the city so far. One death each was reported at the Ram
Manohar Lohia Hospital and ESI Hospital in Basaidarapur. However, Delhi
Health Minister Dr Harsh Vardhan claimed that there was a fall in dropsy
cases since only 38 new cases were admitted as against 118 patients on 3
Sep 1998.
